issues.subject: Contribution information for products with no item detail page
issues.description:
When you click on an individual item of products like GMV and Event Plots, in addition to the item details, the last panel at the bottom ("Contributions") shows when and who contributed that item. For products like SWS-DB and Envelopes that do not support detail pages, this information is not displayed. For these products I recommend to display information on the latest contribution at the bottom of the main page. This will help us to monitor state of health of the product (when the products was last updated). For SWS-DB we can tell if the daily updates have made it into the database and in case of the envelope functions we can easily track successful additions to the product.

Thanks

issues.subject: Fetch current best event information from our fdsnws-event web service instead of directly from Oracle
issues.description:
SPUD fetches the "current best" event information using a database call to Oracle.  All such instances of this lookup should be replaced with a web service call to:

http://service.iris.edu/fdsnws/event/1

The service allows selection of a single event using the 'eventid' parameter which, I believe, is how SPUD accesses event information.

Outward display of details should remain the same, only the internal fetching mechanism should change.

issues.subject: Dealing with /data/reports
issues.description:
Data reports are put in the directory @/data/reports/@. Due to this, we are never going to get away from doing a global redirect from static content at @/data@ to Django-powered content at @/dms/nodes/dmc/data@.

That may be good or bad. It is unclear.

Having an authoritative location for reports is a _good_ thing, whether it should be under @/data@ is another question (it is probably fine the way it is). However, it should be recorded that we cannot move/tinker with anything under data without discussion with Rick and Mea.
